Venezuelan Aluminum Maker Declares Emergency, El Nacional Says

-- B y   N a t h a n   C r o o k s
-- 
2011-04-29T19:09:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/venezuelan-aluminum-maker-declares-emergency-el-nacional-says.html
Venezuelan state-owned aluminum
company CVG Alcasa has declared a state of operational and
financial emergency, newspaper El Nacional  reported .  The company only has resources to operate at 40 percent of
installed capacity, the Caracas-based newspaper reported today,
citing Alcasa President Elio Sayago. New investment of $403
million is needed to bring the company back to full operational
capacity, El Nacional reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Crooks in Santiago at 
 ncrooks@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  